  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some ways you can get into Johns Hopkins University?",
  "response": "Getting into Johns Hopkins University (JHU) is competitive, and applicants typically follow several strategies to strengthen their applications. Here are some effective ways to enhance your chances of admission:\n\n1. **Strong Academic Performance**: Maintain a high GPA, particularly in challenging courses such as Advanced Placement (AP), International Baccalaureate (IB), or honors classes. JHU looks for students who have excelled in rigorous coursework.\n\n2. **Test Scores (if applicable)**: Although JHU has adopted a test-optional policy for recent admissions cycles, strong standardized test scores (SAT/ACT) can still enhance your application if you choose to submit them. Research the average scores of admitted students to aim for competitiveness.\n\n3. **Extracurricular Involvement**: Engage in meaningful extracurricular activities that demonstrate leadership, commitment, and diversity of interests. Quality is more important than quantity, so focus on a few activities that genuinely interest you.\n\n4. **Strong Letters of Recommendation**: Obtain letters of recommendation from teachers or mentors who can speak to your strengths, character, and contributions in the classroom and community.\n\n5. **Compelling Personal Statement**: Write a personal statement or essays that reflect your personality, values, and motivations. Be authentic and convey what makes you unique. Discuss experiences that have shaped you and your aspirations.\n\n6. **Research Experience**: For students applying to a science or engineering program, research experience can be particularly valuable. Pursuing independent research projects or internships can demonstrate your commitment and interest in your field.\n\n7. **Demonstrated Interest**: Showing interest in the university can help, especially if you visit the campus, attend information sessions, or engage with admissions representatives. This can convey your enthusiasm for JHU.\n\n8. **Diversity of Backgrounds**: JHU values diverse perspectives and backgrounds. Share aspects of your identity, culture, or experiences that contribute to your unique viewpoint.\n\n9. **Special Talents or Skills**: If you have exceptional talents (in arts, sports, etc.), highlight these in your application. Unique skills can set you apart from other applicants.\n\n10. **Community Service and Leadership**: Showcase your involvement in community service or leadership roles. JHU values students who contribute positively to their communities.\n\n11. **Prepare for Interviews**: If you have the opportunity for an interview, prepare by researching the university and reflecting on your motivations for wanting to attend. Be ready to articulate why JHU is a good fit for you.\n\nUltimately, it's important to present a well-rounded application that reflects your academic achievements, personal experiences, and future aspirations. The admissions committee looks for students who will contribute positively to the campus community and succeed in their academic pursuits.",
